summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Carr Place, in the City of Seattle, from the south line of produced of Block Forty (40), Lake Union Addition to the City of Seattle, to North Thirty-ninth Street, by grading and curbing the same, in accordance with Majority Petition, being File No. 32307, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle.
